Armagh County Museum has been around since 1937, making it the oldest County Museum in Ireland. Originally built in 1835 as Charlemont Place National School, it now showcases a rich collection of artifacts including archaeology evidence, transport, costume, and art. If you're into history and art, visiting this museum would be a great experience. They feature paintings by local artists and also have works that depict the buildings and landscape of County Armagh.
